SERVER CREATION

BASIC COMMANDS

1)Creating package.json - npm init
2)Install express - npm i express
3)Install JWT - npm i jsonwebtoken
4)Install mongoose - npm i mongoose
5)Install cors - npm i cors


BASIC STEPS

1. Creating a folder 
2. Create a package.json file
3. Install express
4. Creating index.js file
5. Import express inside the index.js
6. Create an app using the express
7. Setup port number
8. Resolving HTTP Requests
9. HTTP Response code
   1xx - Information
   2xx - Success
   3xx - Redirection
   4xx - Client Error
   5xx - Server Error

10. JWT (JSON web token)token - For authentication
    sign()

11. Middleware
    1. Application specific middleware - for entire application
    2. Router specific middleware - token validate - verify()
12. Database Integration
   install mongoose
   bd connect via mongoose
   create model using mongoose
13. Asynchronous function resolving
    Resolve - .then()
    Reject  -  catch()
14. CORS - Cross Origin Resource Sharing
    Install Cors
